The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency, NDLEA has seized 548,000 tablets of tramadol branded as tarkadol and arrested the culprit at 3 Atunya street, Maryland estate, Nkwelle, Oyi local government area of Anambara state. The Director, Media & Advocacy of the Agency Femi Babafemi in a statement revealed that the said culprit Okeke Chijioke, has been on the wanted list of NDLEA and also a major kingpin in Anambra state. He further noted that a notorious interstate drug dealer, Godiya Linus, based in Taraba has also been arrested with efforts of a follow up operation leading to the arrest of Godiya who supplies drugs to Ali in Taraba state.